          "TITLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                " (n,2n) cross section of Be9"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "AUTHOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "H.M.Agnew"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "REFERENCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "code": "R,LA-1371,1952",
                "code_unit": [
                  {
                    "unit": "R,LA-1371,1952",
                    "doi": null,
                    "field": {
                      "reference_type": "R",
                      "reference": {
                        "code": "LA-",
                        "number": "1371",
                        "volume": null,
                        "part": null,
                        "issue": null,
                        "page": null
                      },
                      "date": 1952
                    }
                  }
                ],
                "unit_combination": "(%)"
              },
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INSTITUTE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "1USALAS"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "LONGC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A long counter which had a flat response."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SHELT"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " By measuring the transmission of shells of",
                "graphite of various thicknesses. A series of shells",
                "having a diameter up to 9 in. all gave a transmission",
                "of unity."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "The cross section was computed as I = I0*exp((sigma",
                "n,2n - sigma a)Nt), where I is the number of",
                "neutrons per standard time interval detected by the",
                "long counter with the sphere of Be surrounding the",
                "neutron source. I0 is the number of neutrons detected",
                "under identical conditions except with source bare,",
                "sigma n,2n is the average cross section of Be per",
                "atom for the (n,2n) reaction for the neutron spectrum",
                "involved, sigma a is the average absorption cross",
                "section of Be per atom for the neutron spectrum",
                "involved, and t is the wall thickness in source."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The relatively large errors (average",
                "deviation from the mean) are due primarily to the",
                "misfit cavities in the Be spheres, cracks in in size of",
                " the Be spheres."
              ]
            },
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "ERR-S",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": 1.0,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " In the experiment reported the here",
                " the source was 80 cm from statistical errors involved",
                "were less than 1%."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: The difference between (n,2n) and",
                "the absorption cs would have to be negative, because",
                "\"absorption\" as defined in EXFOR includes (n,2n). In",
                "old papers \"absorption\" is often used for \"capture\", so",
                " (N,ABS) was replaced with (N,G)."
              ]
            }
          ],
